The paper deals with the problem of finding a polygonal curve that matches a given polygonal curve with respect to the Fr\'echet distance, while visiting all points in a given point set. This problem involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms (cs.DS), as well as discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper briefly mentions an algorithm that computes the matching curve, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) if the algorithm involves machine learning or other AI techniques.
